  Purpose: Main polling loop — claims and processes jobs
  - worker_id = f'titan-{socket.gethostname()}-{os.getpid()}'
  - Poll interval: env var TITAN_POLL_INTERVAL_SECONDS (default: 5)
  - On each poll: call claim_next_job → if job found, process it → mark complete/failed
  - Call the EXISTING reconciliation function (reference the actual function name found in codebase)
  - Lease heartbeat: background thread extends lease every TITAN_LEASE_HEARTBEAT_SECONDS (default: 300)
  - Graceful shutdown: catch SIGTERM → set shutdown_flag → finish current job → exit cleanly
  - Structured logging: every state transition logged as JSON:
    {"event":"job_claimed","job_id":"...","masterbook_id":...,"worker_id":"...","ts":"..."}
    {"event":"job_completed","job_id":"...","duration_ms":...,"worker_id":"...","ts":"..."}
    {"event":"job_failed","job_id":"...","error":"...","retry_count":...,"ts":"..."}

MODULE 3: titan_config_loader.py (enhanced version of existing config loader)
  Purpose: Unified config loading — file-based + DB-backed with cache
