  - Internal TTL cache: 60 seconds (use functools.lru_cache or a simple dict + timestamp)
  - validate_config(config: dict) -> None   (raises ConfigValidationError on bad schema)

MODULE 4: titan_worker_supervisor.py
  Purpose: Manages N worker processes and exposes health endpoint
  - N workers: env var TITAN_WORKER_COUNT (default: use CPU count × 2, max 16)
  - Launch workers with multiprocessing.Process
  - Health monitor loop: check each worker every 10 seconds, restart if dead
  - Minimal HTTP health endpoint on port TITAN_HEALTH_PORT (default: 8099):
    GET /health → {"status":"healthy","workers":N,"uptime_seconds":X}
    GET /health/jobs → {"active_jobs":[{"job_id":"...","worker_id":"...","started_at":"..."}]}
  - Graceful shutdown: SIGTERM → stop spawning → wait for workers to finish → exit

